s, Seine-et-Marne|Chelles]], [[Gournay-sur-Marne]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|I}}{{rint|Paris|I|P}} {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|113}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|213}} {{rint|bus|1}} Apolo7 A, B, C, E, F, 13 {{rint|bus|1}} TRA 613 {{rint|bus|1}} Seine-et-Marne Express 19 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N23}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N141}}\n\n|- align=center \n| rowspan=12 bgcolor=#efefef | {{color|#c760ad|'''E4'''}} || {{prs|Rosny \u2013 Bois-Perrier}} || 3 || [[Rosny-sous-Bois]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|102}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|116}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|121}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|145}} {{rint|bus|1}} Titus 2 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Rosny-sous-Bois}} || 3 || [[Rosny-sous-Bois]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|116}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|118}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|143}} {{rint|bus|1}} Titus 1, 2, 3, 4 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center \n| {{prs|Val de Fontenay}} || 3 || [[Fontenay-sous-Bois]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|R}}{{rint|Paris|R|A}} {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|116}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|118}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|122}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|124}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|301}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|524}} {{rint|bus|1}} Les Autobus du Fort 702 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N34}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N71}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Nogent \u2013 Le Perreux}} || 3 || [[Nogent-sur-Marne]], [[Le Perreux-sur-Marne]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|114}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|116}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|120}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|210}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|317}} {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N35}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N71}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center \n| {{prs|Les Boullereaux \u2013 Champigny}} || 3 || [[Champigny-sur-Marne]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|106}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|110}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|116}} {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N130}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Villiers-sur-Marne \u2013 Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise}} || 4 || [[Villiers-sur-Marne]], [[Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|106}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|110}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|206}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|207}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|210}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|306}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|308}} {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N33}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N130}}\n\n|- align=center \n| {{prs|Les Yvris \u2013 Noisy-le-Grand}} || 4 || [[Noisy-le-Grand]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|310}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|312}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|320}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|\u00c9merainville \u2013 Pontault-Combault}} || 5 || [[\u00c9merainville]], [[Pontault-Combault]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|206}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|212}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|421}} {{rint|bus|1}} SITUS 2 {{rint|bus|1}} Seine-et-Marne Express 18 {{rint|bus|1}} Sit'bus A, B, C, D {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center \n| {{prs|Roissy-en-Brie}} || 5 || [[Roissy-en-Brie]]\n| align=left| {{rint|bus|1}} Sit'bus 501A, A, D, E {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Ozoir-la-Ferri\u00e8re}} || 5 || [[Ozoir-la-Ferri\u00e8re]]\n| align=left| {{rint|bus|1}} Arlequin 5, 14 {{rint|bus|1}} Stigo 11, 201 {{rint|bus|1}} PEP'S 13 {{rint|bus|1}} Seine-et-Marne Express 16 {{rint|bus|1}} Sit'bus A {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center \n| {{prs|Gretz-Armainvilliers}} || 5 || [[Gretz-Armainvilliers]]\n| align=left| {{rint|bus|1}} Sol'R 3, 121 {{rint|bus|1}} Stigo 11, 18 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Tournan}} || 5 || [[Tournan-en-Brie]]\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|I}}{{rint|Paris|I|P}} {{rint|bus|1}} Sol'R 3, 7, 21, 28, 121, 209, 309, 409 {{rint|bus|1}} Stigo 11, 18 {{rint|bus|1}} Procars 14 {{rint|bus|1}} Yerres - Brie Centrale 23 {{rint|bus|1}} Darche-Gros 30 {{rint|bus|1}} PEP'S 32 {{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N142}}\n|}\n\n==Map==\n[[File:RER E.gif|thumb|400px|center|Geographically accurate path of the RER E]]\n\n==Operation==\n===Names of services===\nLike all the other [[R\u00e9seau Express R\u00e9gional|RER]] lines, each train is named after the route it takes. The first letter designates the destination, the second indicates whether the train will call at every station or not.\n* '''T''' corresponds to [[Tournan Station|Tournan]]; '''V''' corresponds to [[Villiers-sur-Marne - Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise Station|Villiers-sur-Marne]],\n* '''C''' corresponds to [[Chelles - Gournay Station|Chelles - Gournay]],\n* '''H''' corresponds to [[Haussmann - Saint-Lazare Station|Haussmann - Saint-Lazare]].\n\nRegular names of services of trains departing from Paris are, among others, ''TAVA'' (stops at [[Magenta Station|Magenta]], [[Rosa Parks (Paris RER)|Rosa Parks]], [[Pantin Station|Pantin]], [[Noisy-le-Sec Station|Noisy-le-Sec]], [[Val de Fontenay Station|Val de Fontenay]], and all stations from [[Villiers-sur-Marne - Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise Station|Villiers-sur-Marne]] to [[Tournan Station|Tournan]]), ''VOHE'' (stops at every station, all the way to [[Villiers-sur-Marne - Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise Station|Villiers-sur-Marne]]), ''COHI'' (stops at every station all the way to [[Chelles - Gournay Station|Chelles - Gournay]]).\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of stations of the Paris M\u00e9tro]]\n* [[List of stations of the Paris RER]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n=== English ===\n* [http://www.ratp.info/informer/anglais/index.php# RATP's English-language website]\n* [http://www.ratp.info/orienter/cv/carterer.php RATP's interactive map of the RER]\n* [http://www.ratp.info/orienter/cv/carteparis.php RATP's interactive map of the Paris m\u00e9tro]\n\n=== French ===\n* [http://ratp.fr/ RATP official website]\n* [http://membres.lycos.fr/mobidf/ Mobidf website, dedicated to the RER (unofficial)] {{dead link|date=September 2016}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051208073801/http://www.metro-pole.net/ Metro-Pole website, dedicated to Paris public transports (unofficial)]\n\n{{Paris Transport Network}}{{Paris Rail Stations}}\n\n[[Category:R\u00e9seau Express R\u00e9gional|E, RER E]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 1999]]\n", "text_old": "{{expand French|Ligne E du RER d'\u00cele-de-France|topic=transport|date=April 2015}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2011}}\n{{Infobox rail line\n| name           = RER E\n| color          = {{RER color|E}}\n| logo           = {{rint|Paris|R|size=50}} {{rint|Paris|R|E|size=50}}\n| logo_width     = \n| logo_alt       = \n| image          = \n| image_width    = \n| image_alt      = \n| caption        = \n| type           = [[Rapid transit]]/[[commuter rail]]\n| system         = [[R\u00e9seau Express R\u00e9gional]]\n| status         = Operational\n| stations       = 22\n| ridership2     = 60,000,000 journeys per year\n| open           = 14 July 1999<br />(last extension in 2003)\n| close          = \n| operator       = [[SNCF]]\n| start          = [[Haussmann\u2013Saint-Lazare]] (E1)\n| end            = [[Gare de Chelles\u2013Gournay|Chelles\u2013Gournay]] (E2), [[Tournan station|Tournan]] (E4)\n| stock          = [[SNCF Class Z 22500|Z 22500]], [[Z 50000]]\n| linelength_km  = 52.3\n| gauge          = {{RailGauge|1435mm|lk=on}}\n| speed_km/h     = \n| elevation_m    = \n| website        = \n| map            = [[File:RER E.svg|frameless|upright=1.5|center]]<br />Geographically accurate path of the RER E\n}}'''RER E''' is one of the five lines in the [[R\u00e9seau Express R\u00e9gional]] (English: Regional Express Network), a hybrid [[Commuter rail|suburban commuter]]/[[rapid transit]] system serving [[Paris]], [[France]] and its suburbs. The {{convert|52.3|km|mi|abbr=on}} RER E line travels between Paris and eastern suburbs, with all trains serving the stations in central Paris, before branching out towards the ends of the line.{{RER E}}\nThe line runs from the western terminus [[Haussmann - Saint-Lazare Station|Haussmann - Saint-Lazare]] (E1) to the eastern termini [[Chelles - Gournay Station|Chelles - Gournay]] (E2) and [[Tournan Station|Tournan]] (E4). It is operated by [[SNCF]]. \n\nOriginally referred to as the Est Ouest Liaison Express or EOLE (English: East West Express Link), RER E is the newest line in the system opening in 1999, with the extension in 2003, and further extensions to the west currently under construction.\n\n==History==\n[[File:RER-E Haussmann 2.jpg|thumb|250px|Train arriving at [[Haussmann - Saint-Lazare Station|Haussmann - Saint-Lazare]] on the RER&nbsp;E.]]\n[[File:RER-E Magenta.jpg|thumb|250px|Station [[Magenta Station|Magenta]] on the RER E]]\n\nRER E opened on 14 July 1999 between Haussmann - Saint-Lazare and Chelles - Gournay. The construction included a {{convert|2|km|abbr=on}} tunnel between Haussmann \u2013 St-Lazare and [[Magenta (Paris RER)|Magenta]] (which serves [[Gare de l'Est]] and [[Gare du Nord]]).\n\nThe line was first extended with a new branch from [[Noisy-le-Sec Station|Noisy-le-Sec]] to [[Villiers-sur-Marne - Le Plessis-Tr\u00e9vise Station|Villiers-sur-Marne]] on 30 August 1999. This branch was extended to Tournan on 14 December 2003.\n\nOn 13 December 2015, [[Rosa Parks (Paris RER)|Rosa Parks]] station opened in the [[19th arrondissement of Paris]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.stif.info/ouverture-de-la-gare-rosa-parks-sur-la-ligne-e-du-rer.html | title = RER E: Ouverture de la gare Rosa Parks sur la ligne E du RER | publisher = STIF | date = December 2015 | accessdate = 2015-12-13 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151214195640/http://stif.info/ouverture-de-la-gare-rosa-parks-sur-la-ligne-e-du-rer.html | archivedate = 14 December 2015 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Extension==\n[[File:Carte rer e ouest.png|thumb|Map of the extension to Mantes-la-Jolie]]\nRER E is to be extended from Haussmann - Saint-Lazare to [[La D\u00e9fense Station|La D\u00e9fense]], from where it will take over the branch of [[RER A]] to [[Nanterre]], [[Sartrouville]] and [[Poissy]]. It would then take over a section of SNCF tracks (currently carrying [[Transilien]] J) to reach [[Mantes-la-Jolie]]. Partial revenue service is expected to begin in 2022, full service in 2024.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.stif.org/IMG/pdf/STIF_-_CA_05032014_CP_Prolongement_du_RER_E.pdf | title = PROLONGEMENT DU RER E \u00c0 L\u2019OUEST : APPROBATION DE L\u2019AVANT-PROJET | publisher = STIF | date = 2014-03-05 | accessdate = 2014-03-26 | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140322001704/http://www.stif.org/IMG/pdf/STIF_-_CA_05032014_CP_Prolongement_du_RER_E.pdf | archivedate = 22 March 2014 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nAn eight kilometre tunnel will be dug between Haussmann \u2013 St-Lazare and La D\u00e9fense. An intermediate station at Porte Maillot will offer a transfer to [[RER C]]. The extension is expected to reduce the load on central sections of [[RER B]] (between Gare du Nord and Ch\u00e2telet) and [[RER A]] (between La D\u00e9fense and Auber) by 10-15%. Additionally, transfers will be shifted away from current transfer hub Ch\u00e2telet.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.stif.org/IMG/pdf/DPI_RER_E.pdf | title = RER E: Prolongement d\u2018Haussmann-Saint-Lazare \u00e0 Mantes-la-Jolie | publisher = STIF | date = February 2013 | accessdate = 2014-03-26 | format = pdf | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140322030058/http://www.stif.org/IMG/pdf/DPI_RER_E.pdf | archivedate = 22 March 2014 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==List of RER E stations==\n{| border=\"0\" style=\"border: 1px solid #999  background-color:white\"\n|- bgcolor=#{{RER color|E}}\n! {{color|white|Branch}} !! {{color|white|Station}} !! {{color|white|Zone}} !! {{color|white|Served municipalities}} !! {{color|white|Connections}}\n|- align=center\n| rowspan=5 bgcolor=#efefef | {{color|#{{RER color|E}}|'''E1'''}} || {{prs|Haussmann \u2013 Saint-Lazare}} || 1 || Paris\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|M}}{{rint|Paris|M|3}}{{rint|Paris|M|9}}{{rint|Paris|M|12}}{{rint|Paris|M|13}}{{rint|Paris|M|14}} {{rint|Paris|r}}{{rint|Paris|r|a}} {{rint|Paris|I}}{{rint|Paris|I|J}}{{rint|Paris|I|L}} {{rint|FR|rail}} {{rint|FR|ter}}<br />{{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|20}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|21}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|22}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|24}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|26}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|27}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|28}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|29}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|32}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|43}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|53}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|66}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|80}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|81}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|94}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|95}}<br />{{rint|Paris|N}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N01}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N02}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N15}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N16}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N51}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N52}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N53}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N150}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N151}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N152}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N153}} {{RATP Paris/transfer night|N154}}\n\n|- align=center | bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n| {{prs|Magenta}} || 1 || Paris\n| align=left| {{rint|Paris|M}}{{rint|Paris|M|2}}{{rint|Paris|M|4}}{{rint|Paris|M|5}} {{rint|Paris|R}}{{rint|Paris|R|B}}{{rint|Paris|R|D}} {{rint|Paris|I}}{{rint|Paris|I|H}}{{rint|Paris|I|K}} {{rint|FR|rail}}   [[Eurostar]] [[Thalys]] {{rint|FR|TGV}} {{rint|FR|ter}}<br />{{rint|Paris|B}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|26}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|30}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|31}} {{RATP Paris/transfer|38}} {{RATP Paris/tran