0301063229/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/SRR/Volume14/kgs3.html Central Asian Backlash Against US Franchised Revolutions] Written by K. Gajendra Singh, India's former ambassador to Turkey and Azerbaijan from 1992 to 1996.\n*[http://www.democracyinlebanon.org The Centre for Democracy in Lebanon]\n*Hardy Merriman, [http://www.opendemocracy.net/hardy-merriman/trifecta-of-civil-resistance-unity-planning-discipline The trifecta of civil resistance: unity, planning, discipline], 19 November 2010 at [[openDemocracy.net]]\n*[http://www.civilresistance.info Howard Clark civil resistance website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080928074428/http://en.fondsk.ru/article.php?id=1372 How Orange Networks Work]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110627054009/http://www.civilresistancestudies.org/ ICNC\u2019s Online Learning Platform for the Study & Teaching of Civil Resistance], Washington DC\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110515071750/http://www.nonviolent-conflict.org/index.php/about-icnc International Center on Nonviolent Conflict] (ICNC), Washington DC\n*Jack DuVall, [http://www.opendemocracy.net/jack-duvall/civil-resistance-and-language-of-power \"Civil resistance and the language of power\"], 19 November 2010 at [[openDemocracy.net]]\n*Michael Barker, [https://web.archive.org/web/20070225055624/http://www.zmag.org/content/showarticle.cfm?SectionID=74&ItemID=11311 Regulating revolutions in Eastern Europe: Polyarchy and the National Endowment for Democracy], 1 November 2006.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070612225000/http://cis.politics.ox.ac.uk/research/Projects/civ_res.asp Oxford University Research Project on Civil Resistance and Power Politics]\n*[http://www.csmonitor.com/2005/1031/p09s01-coop.html \"Sowing seeds of democracy in post-soviet granite\" \u2013 the future of democracy in post-Soviet states] Written by Lauren Brodsky, a PhD candidate at the Fletcher School in Medford, Mass., focusing on US public diplomacy and the regions of Southwest and Central Asia.\n*Ste