{"title_page": "Wray Serna", "text_new": "'''Wray Serna''' born December 24, 1983 is an American independent [[fashion designer]] and [[entrepreneur]] based in New York City. She is the founder of WRAY, a clothing, swimwear, and accessories brand known for its eclectic prints and beautifully constructed, easy to wear pieces <ref name=\"Garmentory Magazine\">{{cite news |work=Garmentory Magazine |title=Meet the Designer: Wray Serna |url=http://magazine.garmentory.com/2016/02/23/new-york-designer-wray-serna/ |first=Elisa |last=Kosenen |date=February 23, 2016}}</ref>, and Cofounder and Chief Design Officer of cloth.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.clothapp.com/team-1|title=Cofounder and Chief Design Officer|date=2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nSerna was born in [[Logan, Utah]] and moved with her family to Illinois and California. She is a graduate of the [[California College of the Arts]] where she studied fashion design, painting, and drawing, with extended studies at [[Parsons School of Design]], Paris.\n\n==Career and brand==\n\n===Fashion===\nFounded in 2015 by Wray Serna, WRAY is a New York-based contemporary womenswear collection. Each season, Serna builds on influences from modern and contemporary sculpture and painting to create clothing focused on form and function. While her collections are designed and developed in NYC, every garment is created ethically at [[fair-trade]], family-owned operations in India. In early 2020, just as WRAY's designs were in the process of [[pattern grading]] to extended sizes, [[wardrobe stylist]]  Rebecca Grice approached her for [[Shrill (TV series)]], starring [[Aidy Bryant]]. Grice is an avid supporter of independent brands and acknowledges Wray as one of a handful of independent designers that go the extra mile for plus sizes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/02/9357346/wray-launches-plus-size-aidy-bryant-shrill| title=This Aidy Bryant-Loved Indie Brand Launched Extended Sizes}}</ref> Wray's clothes are worn by celebrities and artists including [[Dakota Johnson]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/article/dakota-johnson-wears-ethically-made-label-wray|title=Vogue: Dakota Johnson\u2019s Perfect Summer Dress Is By an Ethical Fashion Brand}}</ref>, [[Molly Bernard]], [[Hilary Duff]], [[Aidy Bryant]], and Japanese organizing consultant, [[Marie Kondo]].\n\n===Technology===\nSerna is co-founder and Chief Design Officer of Cloth<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/06/20/dress-iphone-app/?_r=0|title=Cloth, a Fashion App, Is Now Weather Sensitive}}</ref>, a fashion app. A unique profiling system gives retailers a better sense of who their customers are and what is in their closets, allowing them to better target and engage their customers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nyftlab.com/cloth|title=NY Fashion Tech Lab: Cloth}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/celiashatzman/2014/11/11/the-new-cloth-app-makes-your-virtual-closet-dreams-come-true/#18947a7c75ff|title=Forbes: The New Cloth App Makes Your Virtual Closet Dreams Come True}}</ref>\n\n==Personal Life==\nSerna and her partner, artist Ethan Fielding Cook<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-ethan-cook-review-20180731-story.html|title=Los Angeles Times: Review: Ethan Cook\u2019s paintings are not paintings. Or are they?}}</ref>, divide their time between their Clinton Hill apartment<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/ethan-cooks-home-is-just-as-vibrant-as-his-artwork|title=Architecural Digest: Ethan Cook\u2019s Home Is Just as Vibrant as His Artwork}}</ref> and their country home in the Catskills.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/06/inside-an-airy-diy-renovation-in-the-catskills.html|title=New York Magazine, The Cut: Inside an Airy, DIY Renovation in the Catskills}}</ref>\n\n==  References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://wray.nyc/ WRAY NYC] official website\n* [https://clothapp.com/ Cloth] official website\n* [https://www.instagram.com/wraynyc/ Wray Serna] on Instagram\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Serna, Wray}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American fashion businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Women fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Women in technology]]\n[[Category:California College of the Arts alumni]]\n", "text_old": "'''Wray Serna''' born December 24, 1983 is an American independent [[fashion designer]] and [[entrepreneur]] based in New York City. She is the founder of WRAY, a clothing, swimwear, and accessories brand known for its eclectic prints and beautifully constructed, easy to wear pieces <ref name=\"Garmentory Magazine\">{{cite news |work=Garmentory Magazine |title=Meet the Designer: Wray Serna |url=http://magazine.garmentory.com/2016/02/23/new-york-designer-wray-serna/ |first=Elisa |last=Kosenen |date=February 23, 2016}}</ref>, and Cofounder and Chief Design Officer of cloth.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.clothapp.com/team-1|title=Cofounder and Chief Design Officer|date=2014}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nSerna was born in [[Logan, Utah]] and moved with her family to Illinois and California. She is a graduate of the [[California College of the Arts]] where she studied fashion design, painting, and drawing, with extended studies at [[Parsons School of Design]], Paris.\n\n==Career and brand==\n\n===Fashion===\nFounded in 2015 by Wray Serna, WRAY is a New York-based contemporary womenswear collection. Each season, Serna builds on influences from modern and contemporary sculpture and painting to create clothing focused on form and function. While her collections are designed and developed in NYC, every garment is created ethically at [[fair-trade]], family-owned operations in India. In early 2020, just as WRAY's designs were in the process of [[pattern grading]] to extended sizes, [[wardrobe stylist]]  Rebecca Grice approached her for [[Shrill (TV series)]], starring [[Aidy Bryant]]. Grice is an avid supporter of independent brands and acknowledges Wray as one of a handful of independent designers that go the extra mile for plus sizes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/02/9357346/wray-launches-plus-size-aidy-bryant-shrill| title=This Aidy Bryant-Loved Indie Brand Launched Extended Sizes}}</ref> Wray's clothing are worn by celebrities and artists including [[Dakota Johnson]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vogue.com/vogueworld/article/dakota-johnson-wears-ethically-made-label-wray|title=Vogue: Dakota Johnson\u2019s Perfect Summer Dress Is By an Ethical Fashion Brand}}</ref>, [[Molly Bernard]], [[Hilary Duff]], [[Aidy Bryant]], and Japanese organizing consultant, [[Marie Kondo]].\n\n===Technology===\nSerna is co-founder and Chief Design Officer of Cloth<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/06/20/dress-iphone-app/?_r=0|title=Cloth, a Fashion App, Is Now Weather Sensitive}}</ref>, a fashion app. A unique profiling system gives retailers a better sense of who their customers are and what is in their closets, allowing them to better target and engage their customers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nyftlab.com/cloth|title=NY Fashion Tech Lab: Cloth}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/celiashatzman/2014/11/11/the-new-cloth-app-makes-your-virtual-closet-dreams-come-true/#18947a7c75ff|title=Forbes: The New Cloth App Makes Your Virtual Closet Dreams Come True}}</ref>\n\n==Personal Life==\nSerna and her partner, artist Ethan Fielding Cook<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-ethan-cook-review-20180731-story.html|title=Los Angeles Times: Review: Ethan Cook\u2019s paintings are not paintings. Or are they?}}</ref>, divide their time between their Clinton Hill apartment<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/ethan-cooks-home-is-just-as-vibrant-as-his-artwork|title=Architecural Digest: Ethan Cook\u2019s Home Is Just as Vibrant as His Artwork}}</ref> and their country home in the Catskills.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/06/inside-an-airy-diy-renovation-in-the-catskills.html|title=New York Magazine, The Cut: Inside an Airy, DIY Renovation in the Catskills}}</ref>\n\n==  References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://wray.nyc/ WRAY NYC] official website\n* [https://clothapp.com/ Cloth] official website\n* [https://www.instagram.com/wraynyc/ Wray Serna] on Instagram\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Serna, Wray}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American fashion businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Women fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Women in technology]]\n[[Category:California College of the Arts alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Temple29", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFashion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wray_Serna"}
{"title_page": "Old Is New", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Old Is New\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Toto (band)|Toto]]\n| cover      = Toto - Old Is New.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 6, 2018\n| recorded   = 1978\u20132008, 2010-2017\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 42:22\n| label      = [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| producer   = Steve Lukather, David Paich, Steve Porcaro, Joseph Williams\n| prev_title = [[40 Trips Around the Sun]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Old Is New\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Alone\n | single1date = November 15, 2017\n | single2     = Spanish Sea\n | single2date = January 3, 2018\n | single3     = Struck by Lightning\n | single3date = February 9, 2018\n | single4     = Devil's Tower\n | single4date = January 24, 2019\n | single5     = Chelsea\n | single5date = May 24, 2019\n | single6     = Fearful Heart\n | single6date = April 3, 2020<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3fykzgvuCXA</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Old Is New''''' is the fourteenth and final studio album (though counted as the 15th album overall) by the American rock band [[Toto (band)|Toto]], released as part of the band's ''All In'' box set on November 6, 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://totoofficial.com/2018/11/toto-limited-edition-box-set-all-in-out-today/|title=TOTO LIMITED EDITION BOX SET \"ALL IN\" OUT TODAY \u2013 TOTO|website=totoofficial.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wabx.net/news/articles/2018/feb/22/toto-releasing-massive-box-set-all-in-this-fall-to-mark-40th-anniversary/|title=Toto releasing massive box set, \"All In,\" this fall to mark 40th anniversary|first=Midwest Communications|last=Inc|website=WABX 107.5}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://95kqds.com/news/articles/2018/dec/01/totos-career-spanning-all-in-box-set-released-today-along-with-new-single-devils-tower/|title=Toto's career-spanning \"All In\" box set released today along with new single, \"Devil's Tower\"|first=Midwest Communications|last=Inc|website=95 KQDS}}</ref> and separately on April 3, 2020.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/totoband/posts/10157185062240954</ref> The tracks \"Devil's Tower\", \"Spanish Sea\" and \"Oh Why\" feature deceased band members [[Jeff Porcaro|Jeff]] (who died in 1992) and [[Mike Porcaro]] (who died in 2015).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stevelukather.com/music/discography/2019/old-is-new.aspx|title=Old is new|website=2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n\n| title1          = Alone\n| note1           = previously on ''[[40 Trips Around the Sun]]''\n| length1         = 4:32\n| writer1         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra1          = Williams\n\n| title2          = Devil's Tower\n| length2         = 3:44\n| writer2         = music by: Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, lyrics by: Williams\n| extra2          = Lukather & Williams\n\n| title3          = Fearful Heart\n| length3         = 3:52\n| writer3         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra3          = Williams\n\n| title4          = Spanish Sea\n| note4           = previously on ''40 Trips Around the Sun''\n| length4         = 4:25\n| writer4         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra4          = Paich & Williams\n\n| title5          = In a Little While\n| length5         = 4:49\n| writer5         = Steve Porcaro & David Paich\n| extra5          = Lukather\n\n| title6          = Chelsea\n| length6         = 4:51\n| writer6         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra6          = Williams\n\n| title7          = Chase the Rain\n| length7         = 3:16\n| writer7         = S. Porcaro, S. Lukather, J. Williams\n| extra7          = S. Porcaro\n\n| title8          = Oh Why?\n| length8         = 3:55\n| writer8         = David Paich\n| extra8          = Paich\n\n| title9          = Struck by Lightning\n| note9           = previously on ''40 Trips Around the Sun''\n| length9         = 4:17\n| writer9         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra9          = Williams\n\n| title10         = We'll Keep On Running\n| length10        = 4:41\n| writer10        = Chris Emerson, Surahn Sidhu, James Rushent, Steve Lukather, [[Jeff Porcaro]], Jane Jessica Higgs, David Paich, Steve Porcaro, Joseph Williams\n| extra10         = Lukather, Williams & Skrillex\n| total_length    = 42:22\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Toto'''\n*[[Steve Lukather]] \u2013 guitars, backing and lead vocals, bass guitar {{small|(1, 9)}}, sitar {{small|(8)}}, piano {{small|3}}\n*[[Joseph Williams (musician)|Joseph Williams]] \u2013 lead and backing vocals, additional keyboards, keyboard bass {{small|(6)}}\n*[[David Paich]] \u2013 piano, keyboards, backing and lead vocals \n*[[Steve Porcaro]] \u2013 synthesizers, keyboards, lead vocals {{small|(7)}}, backing vocals {{small|(4, 5)}}, synth bass {{small|(7)}}, Hammond organ {{small|(6, 8, 9)}}\n*[[Vinnie Colaiuta]] \u2013 drums {{small|(1, 6, 9)}}\n*[[Lenny Castro]] \u2013 percussion\n*[[Jeff Porcaro]] \u2013 drums {{small|(2\u20135, 8)}}\n*[[Mike Porcaro]] \u2013 bass guitar {{small|(3, 4, 8)}}\n*[[David Hungate]] \u2013 bass guitar {{small|(2, 5)}}\n*[[Shannon Forrest]] \u2013 drums {{small| (7)}}\n\n'''Additional musicians\n*Mark T. Williams \u2013 backing vocals (3, 4), [[Timothy B. Schmit]] \u2013 backing vocals {{small|(4)}}\n*[[Martin Tillman]] \u2013 cello {{small|(8, 9)}}\n*Pat Knox, Lorraine Paich, Weston Wilson \u2013 backing vocals (lightning chant) {{small|(9)}}\nJames Rushent, Surahn Sidhu & Trevor Lukather - additional instrumentation (10)\n\n'''Technical personnel''':\n*Mastered by Elliot Scheiner\n*Audio engineered by James Rushent {{small|(7)}}\n*Engineered by Damien Weatherley {{small|(7)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|83|artist=Toto|album=Old Is New|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.stevelukather.com/music/discography/2019/old-is-new.aspx Old is new]\n\n{{Toto}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums published posthumously]]\n[[Category:Columbia Records albums]]\n[[Category:Toto (band) albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Old Is New\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Toto (band)|Toto]]\n| cover      = Toto - Old Is New.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = November 6, 2018\n| recorded   = 1978\u20132008, 2010-2017\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = 42:22\n| label      = [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n| producer   = Steve Lukather, David Paich, Steve Porcaro, Joseph Williams\n| prev_title = [[40 Trips Around the Sun]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Old Is New\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Alone\n | single1date = November 15, 2017\n | single2     = Spanish Sea\n | single2date = January 3, 2018\n | single3     = Struck by Lightning\n | single3date = February 9, 2018\n | single4     = Devil's Tower\n | single4date = January 24, 2019\n | single5     = Chelsea\n | single5date = May 24, 2019\n | single6     = Fearful Heart\n | single6date = April 3, 2020<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3fykzgvuCXA</ref>\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Old Is New''''' is the 14th and final studio album (though counted as the 15th album overall) by the American rock band [[Toto (band)|Toto]], released as part of the band's ''All In'' box set on November 6, 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://totoofficial.com/2018/11/toto-limited-edition-box-set-all-in-out-today/|title=TOTO LIMITED EDITION BOX SET \"ALL IN\" OUT TODAY \u2013 TOTO|website=totoofficial.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wabx.net/news/articles/2018/feb/22/toto-releasing-massive-box-set-all-in-this-fall-to-mark-40th-anniversary/|title=Toto releasing massive box set, \"All In,\" this fall to mark 40th anniversary|first=Midwest Communications|last=Inc|website=WABX 107.5}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://95kqds.com/news/articles/2018/dec/01/totos-career-spanning-all-in-box-set-released-today-along-with-new-single-devils-tower/|title=Toto's career-spanning \"All In\" box set released today along with new single, \"Devil's Tower\"|first=Midwest Communications|last=Inc|website=95 KQDS}}</ref> and separately on April 3, 2020.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/totoband/posts/10157185062240954</ref> The tracks \"Devil's Tower\", \"Spanish Sea\" and \"Oh Why\" feature deceased band members [[Jeff Porcaro|Jeff]] (who died in 1992) and [[Mike Porcaro]] (who died in 2015).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stevelukather.com/music/discography/2019/old-is-new.aspx|title=Old is new|website=2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n\n| title1          = Alone\n| note1           = previously on ''[[40 Trips Around the Sun]]''\n| length1         = 4:32\n| writer1         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra1          = Williams\n\n| title2          = Devil's Tower\n| length2         = 3:44\n| writer2         = music by: Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, lyrics by: Williams\n| extra2          = Lukather & Williams\n\n| title3          = Fearful Heart\n| length3         = 3:52\n| writer3         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra3          = Williams\n\n| title4          = Spanish Sea\n| note4           = previously on ''40 Trips Around the Sun''\n| length4         = 4:25\n| writer4         = Lukather, Paich, Porcaro, Williams\n| extra4          = Paich & Williams\n\n| title5          = In a Little While\n| length5         = 4:49\n| writer5         = Steve Porcaro & David Paich\n| extra5          = Lukather\n\n| title6          = Chelsea\n| length6         = 4:51\n| writer6         = Lukather, 