coppa Italiana|RU]]\n|[[2017\u201318 UEFA Champions League#quarter-final|QF]]\n|-\n|style=\"background: #efefef\"|2018\u201319\n!style=\"background: gold\"|[[2018\u201319 Serie A|1st]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Coppa Italia#quarter-final|QF]]\n!style=\"background: gold\"|[[2018 Supercoppa Italiana|W]]\n|[[2018\u201319 UEFA Champions League#quarter-final|QF]]\n|}\n\n== Honours ==\n=== Manager ===\n''' Sassuolo '''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acmilan.com/en/news/show/150684|title=SASSUOLO-MILAN HISTORY|publisher=A.C. Milan.com|date=11 January 2014|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Lega Pro Prima Divisione|Serie C1]] (1): [[2007\u201308 Serie C1|2007\u201308]]\n\n''' Milan '''<ref name=soccerway.com>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/coaches/massimiliano-allegri/110817/|title=M. Allegri|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=1 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Serie A]] (1): [[2010\u201311 Serie A|2010\u201311]]\n* [[Supercoppa Italiana]] (1): [[2011 Supercoppa Italiana|2011]]\n\n''' Juventus '''<ref name=soccerway.com/>\n* [[Serie A]] (5): [[2014\u201315 Serie A|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Serie A|2015\u201316]], [[2016\u201317 Serie A|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Serie A|2017\u201318]], [[2018\u201319 Serie A|2018\u201319]]\n* [[Coppa Italia]] (4): [[2014\u201315 Coppa Italia|2014\u201315]], [[2015\u201316 Coppa Italia|2015\u201316]], [[2016\u201317 Coppa Italia|2016\u201317]], [[2017\u201318 Coppa Italia|2017\u201318]]\n* [[Supercoppa Italiana]] (2): [[2015 Supercoppa Italiana|2015]], [[2018 Supercoppa Italiana|2018]]\n* [[UEFA Champions League]] Runner-up: [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League|2014\u201315]], [[2016\u201317 UEFA Champions League|2016\u201317]] <!-- hold -->\n\n=== Individual ===\n* Panchina d'Oro Prima Divisione (1): [[2007\u201308 Serie C1|2007\u201308]]<ref name=uefa.com/>\n* [[Panchina d'Oro]] (4): [[2008\u201309 Serie A|2008\u201309]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/52242/allegri%E2%80%99s-opportunity-juve%E2%80%99s-gain|title=Alle